6. StrongDelegateType is not set.

8. StrongDictionaryKeyClass is not set.
9. EventArgsName is only allowed in Event methods.
10. EventArgsType is only allowed in Event methods.

+#!/usr/bin/env bash
+set -euo pipefail

+# Extract actionable tasks from open PRs by scanning PR bodies, diffs, and proposal markdown
+# Creates GitHub issues and labels PRs accordingly
+
+GH_URL=$(git -C /workspace remote get-url origin)
+GH_OWNER=$(echo "$GH_URL" | sed -E 's#.*github.com/([^/]+)/.*#\1#')
+GH_REPO=$(echo "$GH_URL" | sed -E 's#.*/([^/]+)(\.git)?$#\1#')
+
+# Token: prefer env GH_TOKEN; fallback to remote x-access-token

+fi
+
+if [ "${GH_TOKEN:-}" = "" ]; then
+	echo "Error: No GitHub token found. Set GH_TOKEN or configure origin with x-access-token." >&2
+	exit 1
+fi

+API_ROOT="https://api.github.com"
+COMMON_HEADERS=("-H" "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" "-H" "Authorization: Bearer ${GH_TOKEN}" "-H" "X-GitHub-Api-Version: 2022-11-28" "-H" "User-Agent: pr-task-extractor")

+

+	local color="$1"; shift
+	local description="$1"; shift
+	curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" -X POST "$(repo_url "/labels")" \

+ensure_label "from-pr" "0e8a16" "Created from a pull request task"
+ensure_label "todo-extracted" "5319e7" "PR has follow-up issues created"
+ensure_label "ci" "1d76db" "Related to CI or QA pipeline"
+ensure_label "proposal" "c2e0c6" "Proposal and planning"
+ensure_label "automation" "5319e7" "Scripts and automation"
+ensure_label "docs" "bfdadc" "Documentation"

+
+issue_title_exists() { printf '%s\n' "$EXISTING_TITLES" | grep -Fx -- "$1" >/dev/null 2>&1; }
+
+# Categorize by path

+	local path="$1"
+	if [[ "$path" == ci-* || "$path" == ci-*/** || "$path" == ci-proposals/* || "$path" == *ci*.md ]]; then
+		printf 'ci'
+		return
+	fi
+	if [[ "$path" == scripts/* ]]; then
+		printf 'automation'
+		return
+	fi
+	if [[ "$path" == proposals/* || "$path" == IMPROVEMENT_PROPOSALS.md ]]; then
+		printf 'proposal'
+		return
+	fi
+	printf 'docs'

+
+# Extract tasks from PR body (unchecked checkboxes)
+extract_tasks_from_body() {

+}
+
+# Extract tasks from diff patches
+extract_tasks_from_patch() {
+	# Input: unified diff patch on stdin
+	# Strategy: capture inserted checklist items, bullets under task-like headings, and lines with TODO

+	BEGIN{in_tasks=0}
+	/^[+][^+]/ { line=$0; sub(/^\+/, "", line);

+		if (in_tasks && (line ~ /^[[:space:]]*[-*][[:space:]]/ || line ~ /^[[:space:]]*[0-9]+\.[[:space:]]/)) {

+			gsub(/^[[:space:]]*[0-9]+\.[[:space:]]/, "", line);

+}
+
+add_labels_to_issue_number() {
+	local number="$1"; shift
+	local labels_json="$1"; shift
+	printf '%s' "$labels_json" | jq -c '.' | xargs -I{} curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" -X POST \
+		 -d '{"labels":[]}' "$(repo_url "/issues/${number}/labels")" >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
+}
+
+label_pr() {
+	local pr_number="$1"; shift
+	shift || true
+}
+
+# Fetch PRs
+PRS_JSON=$(curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" "$(repo_url "/pulls?state=open&per_page=100")")
+
+printf '%s' "$PRS_JSON" | jq -c '.[]' | while read -r pr; do
+	pr_number=$(printf '%s' "$pr" | jq -r '.number')
+	pr_url=$(printf '%s' "$pr" | jq -r '.html_url')
+	pr_title=$(printf '%s' "$pr" | jq -r '.title')
+	pr_body=$(printf '%s' "$pr" | jq -r '.body // ""')
+
+	# Accumulate tasks and categories
+	mapfile -t body_tasks < <(printf '%s\n' "$pr_body" | extract_tasks_from_body || true)
+	declare -A category_counts
+	declare -a created_issue_links
+	new_issue_count=0
+
+	# Scan files and patches
+	FILES_JSON=$(curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" "$(repo_url "/pulls/${pr_number}/files?per_page=100")")
+
+	# From diffs
+	printf '%s' "$FILES_JSON" | jq -c '.[]' | while read -r file; do
+		path=$(printf '%s' "$file" | jq -r '.filename')
+		patch=$(printf '%s' "$file" | jq -r '.patch // empty')
+		[ -z "$patch" ] && continue
+		cat_label=$(infer_category "$path")
+		category_counts["$cat_label"]=$(( ${category_counts["$cat_label"]:-0} + 1 ))
+		mapfile -t patch_tasks < <(printf '%s' "$patch" | extract_tasks_from_patch || true)
+		for t in "${patch_tasks[@]:-}"; do
+			[ -z "${t:-}" ] && continue
+			# Normalize task string
+			task=$(printf '%s' "$t" | sed -E 's/^[-*][[:space:]]+//' | sed -E 's/^[[:space:]]+//' | sed -E 's/[[:space:]]+$//')
+			[ -z "$task" ] && continue
+			# Build issue title and body
+			issue_title="[PR #${pr_number}] ${task}"
+			# Deduplicate by title against repo
+			if issue_title_exists "$issue_title"; then
+				continue
+			fi
+			issue_body=$(printf 'Source: %s\n\nDetected in file: `%s`\n\nTask:\n- [ ] %s\n' "$pr_url" "$path" "$task")
+			labels_json=$(jq -c --arg cat "$cat_label" '["todo","from-pr", $cat]')
+			resp=$(create_issue "$issue_title" "$issue_body" "$labels_json")
+			url=$(printf '%s' "$resp" | jq -r '.html_url // empty')
+			if [ -n "$url" ]; then
+				created_issue_links+=("$url")
+				EXISTING_TITLES=$(printf '%s\n%s' "$EXISTING_TITLES" "$issue_title")
+				new_issue_count=$(( new_issue_count + 1 ))
+				printf 'Created issue: %s\n' "$url"
+			fi
+		done
+	done
+
+	# Also create from body tasks
+	for t in "${body_tasks[@]:-}"; do
+		[ -z "${t:-}" ] && continue
+		issue_title="[PR #${pr_number}] ${t}"
+		if issue_title_exists "$issue_title"; then
+			continue
+		fi
+		issue_body=$(printf 'Source: %s\n\nTask from PR body:\n- [ ] %s\n' "$pr_url" "$t")
+		labels_json='["todo","from-pr"]'
+		resp=$(create_issue "$issue_title" "$issue_body" "$labels_json")
+		url=$(printf '%s' "$resp" | jq -r '.html_url // empty')
+		if [ -n "$url" ]; then
+			created_issue_links+=("$url")
+			EXISTING_TITLES=$(printf '%s\n%s' "$EXISTING_TITLES" "$issue_title")
+			new_issue_count=$(( new_issue_count + 1 ))
+			printf 'Created issue: %s\n' "$url"
+		fi
+	done
+
+	if [ "$new_issue_count" -gt 0 ]; then
+		# Label PR with todo-extracted and category labels (top 2 categories)
+		labels_to_add=("todo-extracted")
+		# Determine top categories
+		printf '%s\n' "${!category_counts[@]}" | while read -r k; do printf '%s\t%s\n' "$k" "${category_counts[$k]}"; done | sort -k2,2nr | head -n 2 | awk '{print $1}' | while read -r cat; do [ -n "$cat" ] && labels_to_add+=("$cat"); done
+		labels_payload=$(printf '%s\n' "${labels_to_add[@]}" | jq -R . | jq -sc .)
+		curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" -X POST "$(repo_url "/issues/${pr_number}/labels")" -d "{\"labels\":$(printf '%s' "$labels_payload")}" >/dev/null || true
+
+		# Comment with created issues
+		comment_body="Created follow-up issues:\n\n"
+		for link in "${created_issue_links[@]}"; do comment_body+="- ${link}\n"; done
+		printf '%s' "$comment_body" | jq -Rs '{body:.}' | curl -sS "${COMMON_HEADERS[@]}" -X POST -d @- "$(repo_url "/issues/${pr_number}/comments")" >/dev/null || true
+		printf 'Annotated PR #%s with labels (%s) and comment.\n' "$pr_number" "${labels_to_add[*]}"
+	else
+		printf 'PR #%s: no new issues created.\n' "$pr_number"
+	fi
+

### Bug: Pipeline Subshell Issue Variables Not Persisting Variables modified within `while read` loops in pipelines (like `EXISTING_TITLES`, `category_counts`, `created_issue_links`, and `labels_to_add`) are updated in subshells. Their changes don't persist to the parent shell, leading to duplicate issue creation, incorrect PR labeling, and incomplete PR comments.
Additional Locations (1) - [`.scripts/pr_todo_issues.sh#L54-L85`](https://github.com/Duncan-Haywood/research-essay-forge/blob/213b209c1800222b7b37a641342fcdfe64b2b2fc/.scripts/pr_todo_issues.sh#L54-L85)
